6. Formal Criterion

Minimal Criterion

A pattern X is admissible as a construction anchor if:

RetainedStructure(X, T-set) >= τ

Where:
	•	T-set is a family of transformations:
	•	paraphrase
	•	summarization
	•	implementation
	•	adversarial critique
	•	time delay
	•	abstraction increase/decrease
	•	cross-domain mapping
	•	τ is a governance threshold

Intuition

If X only works in one wording, one mood, one context, or one framing, it is weak.
If X survives many transformations while retaining usable form, it is strong.

